.TH "fm10k_get_host_state_pf" 9 "fm10k_get_host_state_pf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fm10k_get_host_state_pf \- Returns the state of the switch and mailbox
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" fm10k_get_host_state_pf
.BI "(struct fm10k_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "bool *switch_ready "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to hardware structure
.IP "switch_ready" 12
pointer to boolean value that will record switch state

This function will check the DMA_CTRL2 register and mailbox in order
to determine if the switch is ready for the PF to begin requesting
addresses and mapping traffic to the local interface.
